<item>
            <title>[HIVE-8083] Authorization DDLs should not enforce hive identifier syntax for user or group</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-8083</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The compiler expects principals (user, group and role) as hive identifiers for authorization DDLs. The user and group are entities that belong to external namespace and we can&apos;t expect those to follow hive identifier syntax rules. For example, a userid or group can contain &apos;-&apos; which is not allowed by compiler.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
